<P>Rea&s;onable <HI>RELIGION.</HI> OR, The TRUTH Of the CHRISTIAN Religion, DEMONSTRATED.</P>
<P>The <HI>Wi&s;dom</HI> of its Precepts Iu&s;tified: And the <HI>Folly</HI> of <HI>Sinning</HI> again&s;t the&s;e Precepts, <HI>Reprehended.</HI></P>
<P>WITH Inconte&s;table <HI>PROOFS,</HI> That <HI>MEN,</HI> who would <HI>Act Rea&s;onably,</HI> mu&s;t <HI>Live Religiou&s;ly.</HI></P>
<P>By <HI>COTTON MATHER.</HI></P>
<P><HI>Bo&s;ton,</HI> in <HI>N.E.</HI> Printed by <HI>T. Green,</HI> for <HI>Benjamin Eliot,</HI> at his Shop, under the We&s;t End of the Town-Hou&s;e. 1700.</P>
</DIV1>
